content.problemStatement:
The Logical NOT operator (!) is used to reverse the logical state of a condition. If the condition is true (non-zero), the NOT operator changes it to false (0), and if the condition is false (0), the NOT operator changes it to true (1).

**Syntax:**
```c
!condition
```

---

**Example:**
```c
#include

int main() {
    int a = 10;

    // Using Logical NOT operator to negate the condition
    printf("Result: %d\n", !a);  // Since a is non-zero, it will print 0 (false)

    return 0;
}

```

